<item>
            <title>[PIG-800] script1-hadoop.pig in pig tutorial hangs when run in local mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-800</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Any script of the form&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;B = foreach A generate flatten(X); -- X is a bag
C = distinct B;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where X is sometimes an empty bag will hang in local mode.  If distinct is replaced by order by it will also hang.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue is that the flatten in foreach returns STATUS_NULL whenever the bag X is empty.  PODistinct and POSort handle this incorrectly and go into an infinite loop.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
